The paper presents an interactive tool for the visual exploration of t-SNE projections, which is relevant to the fields of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The tool is demonstrated using real data sets, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
